level.heading:
GENERAL PROVISIONS (§ 29-9100)
    The purpose of this chapter is to establish requirements governing Medicaideimbursement for Adult Substance Abuse Rehabilitative Services (ASARS).
    ASARS shall be available to reduce and ameliorate Substance Use Disorder (SUD)hich includes both substance abuse and substance dependence.
    The Department of Health, Addiction Prevention and Recovery AdministrationAPRA) shall be responsible for determining each adult Medicaid beneficiary’sligibility for treatment under the ASARS program pursuant to the requirementset forth in Chapter
      23 of Title 29 DCMR.
    Adult Medicaid beneficiaries may present for treatment under the ASARS Programhrough either of the following:
    A beneficiary may self-elect ASARS treatment;
    A legally authorized representative may select treatment under ASARS on behalff an eligible Medicaid beneficiary; or
    The beneficiary has a legal obligation to seek medically necessary substancebuse treatment services.
    Medicaid reimbursement for ASARS treatment shall not be available for theollowing:
    Treatment for inmates in public institutions, as defined in 42 C.F.R. 435.1010;
    Services provided in nursing facilities, intermediate care facilities forersons with intellectual disabilities, and institutions for mental diseases, asefined in section 1919(a) of the Social Security Act and 42 C.F.R.§ 440.150 and 435.1010;
    Room, board, and transportation costs;
    Services delivered as a component of human subjects research or clinical trials;
    Educational, vocational, and job training services;
    Services rendered by parents or other family members;
    Legal services;
    Strictly social or recreational services;
    Services covered elsewhere in the District’s State Plan, includingabilitative and mental health rehabilitative services; and
    Services which are not medically necessary.
    All services that require prior authorization shall be requested through theeneficiary’s Clinical Care Coordinator, assigned pursuant to § 9104.1.
    ASARS treatment shall be rendered only when the beneficiary is present.
    The following services are available for Medicaid reimbursement under the ASARSrogram:

      (a)
      Assessment and Diagnostic Services as described in § 9103;


      (b)
      Clinical Care Coordination as described in § 9104;


      (c)
      Crisis Intervention as described in § 9105;


      (d)
      Medically Managed Intensive Inpatient Detoxification as described in 9106;


      (e)
      Substance Abuse Counseling as described in § 9107;


      (f)
      Medication Management as described in § 9108; and


      (g)
      Medication Assisted Treatment as described in § 9109.
